        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 4:18PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 417 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Alpine, or 7 miles southeast of Sandy, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sandy, Lehi, Draper, Pleasant Grove, Cottonwood Heights, American
Fork, Alpine, Little Cottonwood Canyon, Granite, Big Cottonwood
Canyon, Little Cottonwood Creek Valley, Mill Creek Canyon, Highland,
Cedar Hills, Alta, Brighton, and Snowbird.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
